<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-064-424 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 214 901</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Sept 2 1991 v25 n35 p57(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>X terminals may oust 3270s at agency. (Statistics Canada mayswitch to Unix-based workstations instead of dumb 3270 terminals)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wexler, Joanie M.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Statistics Canada, the central information gathering agency forCanada's federal government, may replace hundreds of dumbterminals with Unix-based intelligent X terminals.andP;  The agency isevaluating ways to provide users with single-screen access to thevarious hosts that store information for the country's consumerprice index, labor force and population.andP;  Statistics Canada hasbeen beta-testing an X terminal/communications controllerconfiguration at seven locales.andP;  The package was assembled byHarris/Adacom Corp. It is made up of an X terminal with a built-in3270 emulator and an Intel Corp 80386 Unix-based multifunctioncommunications controller.andP;  The X-terminals are manufactured byNetwork Computing Devices Inc. They run X Windows System 'server'software and enable users to manipulate programs and informationon various hosts running X 'client' software.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Harris Adacom Corp. (Marketing)Network Computing Devices Inc. (Products).andO;Topic:     System ConversionClient/server architectureCanada. Statistics CanadaX terminalsDumb terminalsUnix-like operating systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Terminal market. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>